  "texts": [
    "-A Stokes local system V can equivalently be thought of as a local system V on the fission surface Σ(Θ) satisfying certain conditions (see Remark 3.6 for this viewpoint).",
    "-The Stokes local system V can be reconstructed up to isomorphism from its associated formal local system and the data of the parallel transport ρ i→j of V along the Stokes paths γ i→j in the fission surface (see Remark 4.10 and Proposition 4.11 for a more precise statement).",
